        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 8 at 10:29PM CDT until June 8 at 11:15PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1028 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over southern
Abilene, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Golf ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect wind
damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

This severe storm will be near...
Eastern Abilene, Clyde, Potosi, and Hamby around 1035 PM CDT.
Baird around 1050 PM CDT.

Other locations impacted by this severe thunderstorm include Impact
and Kirby Lake.

This includes Interstate 20 between Mile Markers 274 and 310.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
